# Why: Documenso ships a sophisticated CSP middleware
#      (apps/remix/server/security-headers.ts) with per-request nonces,
#      strict `script-src 'strict-dynamic'`, and path-aware `frame-ancestors`
#      (the modern replacement for X-Frame-Options). What it does NOT ship:
#
#        - Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS)
#        - Permissions-Policy
#        - Globalized X-Content-Type-Options + Referrer-Policy
#          (upstream sets these only on /embed routes)
#
#      The reason upstream skips them is reasonable: HSTS in particular
#      is operator-specific (depends on cert chain, subdomain layout, and
#      preload-list submission). What ships universally for one self-host
#      may break another.
#
#      Solution: a BizRethink-namespaced site-setting (id="site.security-
#      headers") with an admin-UI panel under Site Settings. Operator
#      toggles HSTS on after they've verified their cert and subdomain
#      layout; Permissions-Policy is on by default (sane denylist that
#      a contract-signing app never legitimately needs); nosniff and
#      Referrer-Policy are globalized unconditionally (they have no
#      downside on any path).
#
#      Files added (no patches needed):
#        - packages/bizrethink/server-only/site-settings/schemas/security-headers.ts
#          (Zod schema for the site-setting row)
#        - packages/bizrethink/server-only/security-headers-config.ts
#          (DB getter with 60s in-memory cache + invalidate hook)
#
#      Files patched:
#        - apps/remix/server/security-headers.ts
#          Imports the BizRethink config getter; after upstream's CSP block,
#          unconditionally sets nosniff + Referrer-Policy on all page
#          paths, then conditionally adds HSTS + Permissions-Policy from
#          the DB row.
#        - packages/lib/server-only/site-settings/schema.ts
#          Adds ZSiteSettingsSecurityHeadersSchema to the union (already
#          an overlay-modified file from overlay 015).
#        - packages/lib/server-only/site-settings/upsert-site-setting.ts
#          Calls invalidateSecurityHeadersConfig() when the security-
#          headers row is upserted, so admin UI saves take effect on
#          next request without a process restart.
#        - apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/admin+/site-settings.tsx
#          New form section under existing site-settings page with
#          Switch/number/text inputs for all options. Mirrors webhook
#          and captcha sections from overlays 015/017.
#
#      Companion change in the marketing site repo
#      (internal-bizrethink-pacta-web): nginx.conf hardcodes the same
#      headers. Static site has no admin UI by design — operator
#      preferences are not relevant for a stateless Astro export.
#
#      Fragility:
#        LOW for the schema/config-getter additions (new files in our
#        package).
#        LOW for the `security-headers.ts` patch — only appends after
#        upstream's existing logic; doesn't modify the CSP-building code.
#        MEDIUM for the `upsert-site-setting.ts` patch — touches a
#        critical write path that all site-settings flow through. The
#        added cache-invalidate is dynamic-imported in a try/catch so
#        a bizrethink import failure can't break upstream upserts.
#        MEDIUM for the site-settings.tsx admin UI — large file, lots
#        of overlay history. Diff is purely additive (new section at
#        the bottom).
#
#      Long-term: file an upstream issue suggesting Documenso ship HSTS
#      and Permissions-Policy as opt-in env vars
#      (DOCUMENSO_HSTS_MAX_AGE, DOCUMENSO_PERMISSIONS_POLICY). Self-hosters
#      who don't want the admin-UI complexity could just set the env vars
#      and skip the DB row entirely. Until upstream agrees, this overlay
#      gives us full control via the existing site-settings pattern.
